==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|πολύγλωττος||lang=grc|tr=poluglōttos|'many-tongied, polyglot'}}, from {{term|πολύς||tr=polus|lang=grc|many}} + {{term|γλῶττα||lang=grc|tr=glōtta|'tongue, language'}} (Attic variant of [[γλῶςςα]]).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/pɒliːglɒt/}}

===Adjective===
'''polyglot'''

# Versed in, or speaking, many [[language]]s.
# Containing, or made up of, several languages.
#: ''a '''polyglot''' lexicon; a '''polyglot''' Bible''
# Comprising various linguistic groups
#: ''A '''polyglot''' region without a clearly dominant culture may develop an artifical lingua franca, such as Pidgin English in the South Sea

